properties.headline: Wind Advisory issued February 10 at 3:14PM PST until February 11 at 10:00AM PST by NWS Sacramento CA
properties.description:
...Wind advisory has been extended until 10 AM tomorrow morning
for the higher elevations of the northern Sierra Nevada and
extreme southern Cascade Range. The foothills of zone 66,
including Shasta, Butte, and Tehama counties will have a Wind
Advisory that goes into effect at 10 PM this evening...

* WHAT...Northeast winds 15 to 25 mph with gusts up to 40 to 50
mph expected. Southwest facing canyons and exposed ridges will
likely see the strongest winds.

* WHERE...Northeast Foothills/Sacramento Valley County.

* WHEN...From 10 PM this evening to 10 AM PST Tuesday.

* IMPACTS...Gusty winds could blow around unsecured objects. Tree
limbs could be blown down and a few power outages may result.
Difficult driving conditions for small and high profile vehicles.
properties.instruction:
Use extra caution when driving, especially if operating a high
profile vehicle. Secure outdoor objects.

NWSheadline: WIND ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM 10 PM THIS EVENING TO 10 AM PST TUESDAY
